CXL. At this time, after Gratian had set forth his Decree, the Canonists that made their glosses upon it were in great account3 and, next the Ordinary Gloss upon the Bible, no books were more esteemed than theirs. The first, (or the second, at least¹¹,) that glossed the Canon Law, was John Semeca, commonly called Teutonicus, being a German, and the Provost of Halberstade there, in the Duke of Brunswick's country.
